ater Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":5,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Wormegay was born in 1101, in Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England, his father, Sir Richard de Wormegay, was 27 and his mother, unidentified wife of Sir Richard de Wormegay, was 25. He married Beatrix de Pierrepont in 1120, in Wormegay, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1166, in Wormegay, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1101–1166":"1101–1166","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","–1130":"–1130","1130–1179":"1130–1179","1074–1130":"1074–1130","1076–Female":"1076–Surnud","1106":"1106","1105":"1105","1179":"1179","1101":"1101","Abt 1166":"umbes 1166","1166":"1166","1120":"1120","after 1130":"pärast 1130","1076":"1076","1130":"1130","1097":"1097","1074":"1074","Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England":"Wormegay, Norfolk, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wormegay, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1101–1166":"1101–1166","1105–Female":"1105–Kuollut","–1130":"–1130","1130–1179":"1130–1179","1074–1130":"1074–1130","1076–Female":"1076–Kuollut","1106":"1106","1105":"1105","1179":"1179","1101":"1101","Abt 1166":"noin 1166","1166":"1166","1120":"1120","after 1130":"1130 jälkeen","1076":"1076","1130":"1130","1097":"1097","1074":"1074","Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England":"Wormegay, Norfolk, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wormegay, Norfolk, En